|lexicon[vivarium]
  :title vivarium — LEXICON (the bounded, ubiquitous vocabulary)
  :seeded 2026-07-03
  :restructured 2026-07-11
  :status living

  ; Converted from ad-hoc markdown bullets to dictionary-grade |term entries
  ; 2026-07-11 (Joseph's ask: the headword being adopted must be unmistakable;
  ; definition -> relationships -> boundaries, per term). Section numbers SS1-SS8
  ; are frozen — external docs cite "LEXICON SS5" etc. Prior form: git history.

  |meta[entry-schema]
    :authority PROCESS.udon self-governance valve

    One term per |term element — the [slug] and :name are the headword; what we
    are adopting is never buried in a compound label. Body: the FIRST paragraph
    is the definition. Then only-if-real children (a field that is not real is
    omitted):
    - |not        — what it is not / what not to call it
    - |confused   — easily confused with (and how to tell apart)
    - |rel        — relation edges (:to term-slug :kind verb) — these build the
                    vocabulary graph; keep verbs plain (runs, composes-into,
                    floor-of, occupies, edge-of, ...)
    - |context    — binding scope beyond vivarium/archema; register notes
    - |carve      — the collision carved against, compressed; trail -> SUPERSEDED.md
    - |source     — the design doc carrying the full machinery
    Statuses (:status): settled (in live use, collision-checked) · carved
    (chosen against a recorded collision) · open (needs Joseph's decision;
    candidates loosely held). Markdown tables live in !:md: blocks (a bare
    table row would parse as an element). Math stays $...$ LaTeX.

    Why a lexicon at all: (1) carves away from colliding usage must be recorded
    or future sessions re-collide; (2) project-unique terms carry design
    decisions inside them, and vague usage quietly un-decides them. The deeper
    motivation (Joseph, 2026-07-03): the tension web of caching x deterministic
    seeding x world-building x saves x strictly-causal runs x iteration already
    produced slowdowns and re-arguing. Names are how we stop re-arguing.
    A term earns its place by standalone citability ([[naming-principles]]).

    Register convention (2026-07-11, deliberate): Greek = the law-article
    machinery (nomos family) · Latin = the world-governance layer (regula,
    regnum, ordinum) · plain English = the lived concepts (Kingdom, Charge,
    Promise, Record, slot, permit). Register signals layer; a proposal that
    crosses registers should notice it is doing so.

  ; ==========================================================================
  |section[world-structure]
    :num 1
    :name World-structure (phases & gates)

    |term[phase]
      :status carved
      A span in which a set of macro systems runs until converged.
      |carve against "epoch" — three collisions: geology's epochs, the erosion
        solver's step unit, ordinary usage.
      |rel :to charge :kind must-deliver
      |rel :to promise :kind hands-forward
      |rel :to phase-gate :kind bounded-by
      |source tabularium/terrestris.ordinum.udon

    |term[epoch]
      :status settled
      Reserved exclusively for the erosion solver's step unit.
      |not a span of world-history (that is a phase); not a geological epoch.

    |term[phase-gate]
      :status settled
      :since 2026-07-04
      The boundary between phases — the threshold where the previous phase's
      Charge is checked and met.
      |rel :to charge :kind opened-by
      |carve replaced "checkpoint", which bundled the gate + the memo + the
        Record and collided with ASF's agent-state checkpoint — SUPERSEDED.md.

    |term[phase-transition]
      :status settled
      :since 2026-07-04
      The regime-change EVENT at a phase-gate. Incremental, never a wholesale
      swap: most systems perpetuate, a few sunset, a larger group of new and
      finer-scale systems spins up at the gate (.archive/PHASES.md Design notes).
      It leaves the largest memo, and it promotes converged state into Law.
      |rel :to law :kind revises
      |rel :to memo :kind leaves
      |rel :to ordinum :kind floor-checked-against

    |term[charge]
      :status settled
      What a phase must establish — the GATING SUBSET of its promises. A
      phase's charge IS the next phase-gate's opening condition.
      |rel :to promise :kind gating-subset-of

    |term[promise]
      :status settled
      :since 2026-07-11
      A defeasible, forward-facing commitment a phase generates (preconditioned
      on prior phases) that later phases may depend on — the SUPERSET of which
      Charge is the gating subset. Its `.class` is its kind (stackable): state
      (a frozen field/datum handed forward) · regime (nomoi that keep running
      past the gate) · capability (a precondition now unlocked that enables new
      nomoi downstream) · limit (a standing incapability in force, e.g. the
      coal window). A promise names, when exact, the nomos that keeps it
      (`:kept-by`) and the predicate that would convict it (`|predicate`); with
      NEITHER it is an honest GLOSS — a word-of-honor not yet mechanized, and
      the gloss set is greppable/auditable. Maturity ladder: named (prose only)
      → specified (has a predicate) → claimed (has :kept-by) → kept (predicate
      passes at a declared tier). The rule that keeps it honest: **no promise
      may be marked fulfilled at any epistemic level without a predicate** —
      nothing has been defined that could convict it (acceptance-test
      discipline). At the nomos grain a promise is `{quantity, conservation}`
      (`nomotheke.rs`); at the phase grain it is the promotion of its nomoi's
      promises into standing law.
      |not the active-system-set (what MACHINERY runs) — a promise is the
        OUTCOME/affordance guaranteed forward, not the process that keeps it.
      |confused the async CS "Promise/Future" — carved: no async exists in this
        codebase and the world-phase domain disambiguates; the referent is a
        forward commitment, never a deferred value.
      |carve replaced "Bequest" (Joseph, 2026-07-11: ornate, faintly
        legalistic, the odd sibling of Charge/Record; Promise is natively
        defeasible and pairs — Charge → Promise → Record = must-do → committed
        → kept). "provisions/affordances/pledge" also considered. SUPERSEDED.md.
      |rel :to charge :kind generated-by
      |rel :to defeasance :kind voided-by
      |rel :to predicate :kind checked-by
      |rel :to nomotheke :kind declared-in
      |rel :to law :kind promoted-into
      |source tabularium/terrestris.ordinum.udon (reading-rules)

    |term[defeasance]
      :status settled
      :since 2026-07-11
      The mechanism of "defeasible": a later phase's explicit retirement of a
      prior promise (`|defeasance :voids "<phase.promise>" :by <charge>`, with
      an honest reason). Phases declare only their NOVEL promises; inherited
      promises CONTINUE IMPLICITLY (no re-listing — the mind should not carry
      ancient ongoing processes as clutter). So the promises IN FORCE at phase
      N = union(promises 0..N) minus union(defeasances 0..N). Canonical
      instance: Phase 6's decomposers void Phase 5's coal-window limit.
      |confused .archive/PHASES.md's "sunset" (a system stopping) — sunset is the
        friendly gloss for the regime case; defeasance is the precise
        mechanism, and it pairs with the property word "defeasible".
      |rel :to promise :kind voids
      |rel :to permit :kind same-shape-as
      |source tabularium/terrestris.ordinum.udon (reading-rules)

    |term[predicate]
      :status settled
      :since 2026-07-11
      A promise's testable condition — the falsifiable core a probe would check
      to decide whether the promise is kept (`|predicate ...` inside a promise;
      prose now, formal as it sharpens; ≈ an acceptance criterion). A promise
      with no predicate is UN-CHECKABLE (cannot be marked fulfilled at any
      tier) — so big-picture promises land first and their predicates are
      written when we need to see them delivered, which then guides the coding.
      |rel :to promise :kind falsifiable-core-of

    |term[record]
      :status settled
      A promise's readable-in-rock slice, deliberately DEMOTED to sanity
      probe: a lossy shadow (a feather in a fossil is a relic, not a
      fundamental output) — a consistency check that the right past processes
      ran, never sufficient to reconstruct the past, never the canonical state.
      The evidence that a phase's promises were KEPT (drill a core; the phases
      must appear in order, or the machinery is lying).
      |not the phase's "in-world form"; not the canonical state.
      |rel :to promise :kind verifies-keeping-of

    |term[gate-tags]
      :status settled
      The per-charge epistemic tags — #gate (hard prerequisite, we simulate) ·
      #earth (Earth's pattern, kept for fidelity) · #mech (causality known, no
      simulable mechanism yet) · #emergent (verify, don't build). Honesty
      about ARROWS, never about implementation status.
      |rel :to epistemic-axes :kind refined-by

    |term[ordinum]
      :status settled
      :since 2026-07-11
      :forms full formal name Ordinatio Ordinum; keyed ordinum@version
      The codified, pinned, versioned phase-expectations artifact — the
      per-phase Charge/Promise floor as DATA, which every regula cites as the
      floor it may extend but never silently undercut. .archive/PHASES.md is its
      reportatio (the prose working text the authorized version compiles
      from — the medieval ordinatio-vs-reportatio carve, Scotus precedent) and
      archives once codification lands. A PHASES revision yields a NEW ordinum
      version; existing regulae keep their pinned floor and opt in by
      re-versioning — integration-is-replacement applied to the constitution.
      |not a stage-synonym source: stages remain PHASES — "order" is not
        adopted (it would re-blur sequence-vs-class; class-of-regna stays
        extensional, "Terrestris regna").
      |context grammar held honestly — standalone "ordinum" is a bare genitive
        plural; the elided head noun (ordinatio) makes the full form exact.
        Deliberate ellipsis, Joseph's euphony call.
      |carve rejected: taxis (in-domain biology collision — chemotaxis will
        someday run in the world) · syntagma (names the assembly, not the
        norm; "syntagmatic" is live linguistics vocabulary) · ordinatium (not
        a Latin form). SUPERSEDED.md.
      |rel :to regula :kind floor-of
      |rel :to phase :kind codifies
      |source doc/plan/regula-conformance-design.md SS2

    |term[target]
      :status settled
      Phases 6/7/8 as TARGET 1/2/3 — the playable entry points. ETHICS.md
      binds from Phase 7's transition.

    |term[canceling-pair]
      :status settled
      A shield and its threat jointly unbuilt at zero fidelity cost until a
      consumer reads their DIFFERENCE or either member alone (magnetic field x
      solar wind; Jupiter-shepherding x impactor flux).
      |rel :to permit :kind audited-as

    |term[declare-causally-materialize-lazily]
      :status settled
      Principle: parameters are committed at their causal position, computed
      on first downstream pull (the moon is the archetype).

    |term[regime]
      :status settled
      A working, deliberately non-MECE label for the DOMINANCE STRUCTURE of
      the vivarium at a given causal-step: which systems, states, and cycles
      (optionally scales and shock-generators) currently dominate the
      dynamics. Fuzziness is by design — "dominant" is consumer-relative
      (moonlight is negligible until werewolves, or orbital mirrors, make all
      light-sensitive systems lunar). Two anchors keep the fuzziness honest:
      dominant balance (the asymptotics term of art — a regime is a dominant
      balance over the phenomenon set) and biome (precedent that a useful
      classification over continuous fields needs no crisp boundaries).
      |confused ASF's dynamic-regime axis (R0-R3, interaction-dynamics class
        of composite agents) — near ASF material say "world regime" vs
        "dynamic regime Rn". See the collision ledger, SS5.
      |context phase is the crisp term; regime may stay gloss (Joseph).

    |term[regime-change]
      :status open
      Activation, deactivation, or replacement of the dominant systems (or a
      newly-activated system coming to dominate). A phase boundary is a
      regime-change we CERTIFY — memoized, charged, gated; most regime-changes
      we never certify. (Joseph flagged residual vagueness; the
      certify-vs-don't split is the sharpening so far.)

    |term[subphase]
      :status open
      Reserved: an intermediate regime WITHIN a phase — what a regime-change
      becomes when a phase (especially Abyssal) earns internal gates.

    |term[world]
      :status settled
      Any simulated-planet vivarium; the primary/initial KIND of vivarium.
      "(phase-name) world" = a world evolved to that phase at least in the
      areas of granularity and proximal interest (an "Abyssal world wearing a
      Primeval sky") — fidelity is local and consumer-relative (the telescope,
      SS2), never a global claim.

    |term[earth]
      :status carved
      :forms Earth (capital) / earth (lowercase) / #earth (gate tag)
      Capital-E Earth is the real planet, in the real universe, that humans
      experience — never a generated world, however faithful. Lowercase earth
      is ground/soil. #earth is the gate tag (Earth's PATTERN, kept for
      fidelity). Keep the three typographically distinct.
      |context if you name a generated world "Earth" and try to make it
        match, don't be surprised by a copyright-violation notice from the
        real one — unless you generate it faithfully enough that Joseph is
        typing this very sentence inside your world with the stolen name, in
        which case he'll put in a good word that it's a universe-bending
        recursion rather than trademark infringement. (The projects are wholly
        serious; their author declines to be.)

  ; ==========================================================================
  |section[runtime-fidelity]
    :num 2
    :name Runtime & fidelity

    |term[fidelity-ladder]
      :status settled
      Spend representation by consequence; every aspect has a ladder of model
      rungs and may honestly occupy any rung whose sufficient statistics its
      consumers need.
      |rel :to rung :kind composed-of
      |source doc/design/DESIGN-REDUX.md SS12

    |term[telescope]
      :status settled
      Nested resolution tiers around a focus, re-anchored on drift (the
      erosion telescope is the built instance).
      |rel :to focus :kind centered-on

    |term[focus]
      :status settled
      :since 2026-07-10
      The LIVE attention point — an observer's current position (the code's
      VIVARIUM_FOCUS_I/J sense). Ephemeral; contrast beacon.
      |confused beacon — focus is live and transient; a beacon is standing
        and spec-persisted.

    |term[beacon]
      :status settled
      :since 2026-07-10
      A STANDING, spec-persisted build priority: a (region, stage/phase,
      level) triple in the manifest's demand bucket that draws the builder's
      causal-cone advancement toward it. Demand changes what gets built FIRST,
      provably never WHAT gets built (order-independence: nomoi depend on
      artifacts by key, never "latest available") — so beacons are freely
      editable mid-build. Per-beacon policy: depth-first (a waiting explorer)
      vs breadth-first (the globe-spinner).
      |rel :to manifest :kind lives-in
      |source doc/plan/builder-explorer-decoupling.md

    |term[finisher]
      :status settled
      A fine tier run for 1-2 animated passes over its parent's band,
      mean-pinned to conserve (Joseph's field observation, 2026-07-02).

    |term[memo]
      :status settled
      A cached converged state in the lazy query-graph runtime; the memo left
      at a phase-transition is the largest. The save-file IS the memo store.
      |not "checkpoint" (retired; see the collision ledger, SS5).
      |source doc/design/DESIGN-REDUX.md SS11-13

    |term[system]
      :status settled
      The phenomenon-level unit a phase runs — erosion, hydrology, climate
      (doc/design/DESIGN-SYSTEMS.md rows; the ARCHITECTURE SS9 contract is what
      one declares to join the machine).
      |rel :to rung :kind climbs
      |rel :to slot :kind fills-via-nomos

    |term[rung]
      :status settled
      A system's position on its fidelity ladder — crude statistics-honoring
      stand-in up through full physics, both directions legitimate (the
      ladder runs both ways; descent to a validated surrogate is the
      economical move).
      |rel :to fidelity-ladder :kind position-on

    |term[kernel]
      :status settled
      The concrete numerical implementation — the code (Fluvial, WaterSim).
      |rel :to nomos :kind run-by

    |term[nomos]
      :status settled
      :since 2026-07-10
      :forms pl. nomos (invariant — DECISIONS[nomos-plural-invariant], 2026-07-12; was "nomoi"); family nomothete / nomothetic / nomotheke
      The keyed, versioned, memoizable invocation unit — the executable
      embodiment of one ARTICLE of world-law: the grain at which algorithms
      have identity (spine-tile@spine-2026-07-10b-sphere3d) and where the
      epistemic tags attach. A phase is a choreography of nomoi; a nomos runs
      a kernel implementing a system's current rung. Family: nomothete (what
      lays a nomos down) · nomothetic (Windelband's law-positing science —
      precisely what authoring one is) · nomotheke (the registry where every
      nomos declares itself; declarations mint the store keys). Gravity
      precedent: Schmitt's "The Nomos of the Earth."
      |rel :to law :kind composes-into
      |rel :to kernel :kind runs
      |rel :to nomotheke :kind declared-in
      |rel :to slot :kind candidate-occupant-of
      |not cognate with noumenon — nomos is from nemein (to allot), noumenon
        from noein (to think); but the nomoi + seed literally constitute the
        world's noumenon (SS7.2), so the near-homophony is free resonance,
        deliberately enjoyed.
      |carve replaced "recipe" (Joseph's veto: casual-instructions register
        unworthy of executable law governing living things) — SUPERSEDED.md;
        rejected candidates in this entry's git history.

    |term[patch]
      :status settled
      The Cartesian stencil substrate — a chunk interior as a flat row-major
      array with a halo carrying cross-chunk/face neighbours, so hot loops
      never branch. Column/Stratum and CellId — the matter and spatial keys —
      are defined in doc/design/DESIGN-MATERIAL.md and used here unchanged.

    |term[detail-must-be-earned]
      :status settled
      Principle (Joseph): never paint sub-simulation detail the physics did
      not produce; the finest SIMULATED tier is authoritative and painted
      coordinate-noise detail yields to any simulated field overlapping it.

    |term[canonical-frame]
      :status open
      :since 2026-07-10
      The CellId $2^n$ space-time grid with columns/strata: the universal
      causal coordinate map every system must be QUERYABLE in, and the
      reducibility mechanism (parent = bit-shift). It is NOT the mandated
      internal representation.
      |rel :to native-representation :kind projection-target-of

    |term[native-representation]
      :status open
      :since 2026-07-10
      The domain-specific internal shape a system may compute and memoize in
      when it is faster and smaller than columns-on-the-grid — tilted-slab
      stacks with a latent dip; the fluvial cells-to-receivers list (CHONK's
      graph); closed-form coefficient blocks (insolation lives here already).
      What keeps it honest: (a) the native-to-canonical projection is itself a
      nomos — pure, fated, keyed, memoized; (b) conservation and the
      sufficient-statistic contract bind at the projection exactly as at any
      lifting; (c) co-fidelity is enforced on the canonical side. Machinery
      deliberately unsettled until the first real second-representation
      system lands (TODO).
      |context field precedents — Lagrangian/Eulerian projection (PIC/FLIP,
        MPM), spectral methods. In-house precedents — flat chunk interiors
        under Hilbert ordering; voxels as a view over strata; bodies overlay
        columns.

  ; ==========================================================================
  |section[determinism-provenance]
    :num 3
    :name Determinism & provenance

    |term[fated-noise]
      :status settled
      All stochasticity is a stateless pure function of (world-seed,
      coordinate/identity key) — never a shared mutable stream. A value's
      draw is FATED by its identity: fixed, discoverable in any order, the
      same forever. Realized by a KRNG (keyed RNG) / DRNG (deterministic
      RNG) — the stateless, well-mixed generator keyed on (seed, key).
      |not "Fate" as a defined noun — deliberately not adopted; the adjective
        "fated" plus the KRNG/DRNG mechanism carry it.
      |rel :to lawful-steering :kind overridable-by

    |term[generator-pinning]
      :status open
      FILL_ALGO_VERSION generalized: frozen state must pin the algorithm
      version that produced it; a cache key is f(inputs, seed,
      generator-version). Already assumed everywhere; still unnamed. The
      structural resolution (source-derived nomos versions) is queued in
      doc/toolchain.md.

    |term[run-modes]
      :status open
      Different things currently called by one name ("running the world"):
      strictly temporal-causal runs · replays from pinned generators ·
      discardable iteration runs · live play accruing history. Referents now
      pinned even though naming is open: strictly-causal / replay / live-play
      = Closed vs Open-with-recorded-forcing (SS7.2); the discardable
      iteration run = the pre-participation non-intervention register (SS4).

  ; ==========================================================================
  |section[vivium-lifecycle]
    :num 4
    :name World-as-artifact — the lifecycle of a vivium

    ; The lifecycle layer. The participation ONTOLOGY it rests on (Kingdom,
    ; exo/endo, Realized/Lawful, the access matrix) is SS7 — keep the layers
    ; distinct.

    |term[vivium]
      :status settled
      :since 2026-07-04
      :forms pl. vivia
      One instantiated world-artifact you can name, fork, and cite:
      build-stack + Target world + backstory + interventional history. Coined
      by Joseph in use and confirmed. It earns its keep twice: standalone
      citability, and the in-vitro/in-vivo resonance gives ASF a third
      empirical register — results obtained IN VIVIA sit between toy models
      (ground truth, trivial dynamics) and field data (rich dynamics, no
      ground truth): richer than the first, more legible than the second.
      |not vivarium — that is the class / the engine / the project; a vivium
        is one instantiated world.
      |rel :to regula :kind declares-conformance-to
      |rel :to manifest :kind individuated-by

    |note[three-layers]
      :name The three layers inside a vivium (they differ in what persists)

      |term[build-stack]
        :status settled
        Layer 1 — NAME + Primary Invariants + META-parameters + the
        world-building nomos stack. Mutable while the kingdom is Incomplete
        (SS7.2). Changing seed/params/stack forks a NEW world (new identity);
        changing target SCALE does not (a view/awareness knob, not ontology).

      |term[target-world]
        :status settled
        Layer 2 — the generic world evolved to the chosen Target phase; law
        now immutable (Realized, SS7.2), complete-to-phase but not yet peopled
        for a scenario.

      |term[backstory]
        :status carved
        Layer 3 — the scenario-specific realized situation a participant
        inherits as its world's past: the ARTIFACT.
        |not the frozen pre-target phases (a recurring wrong reading — those
          are the Target world, layer 2). The Backstory is produced ON TOP of
          it.
        |rel :to brooding :kind produced-by

      |term[brooding]
        :status settled
        :since 2026-07-09
        The process that produces the Backstory: conditioning a generative
        simulation on a target entry-state. Two mechanisms — Steer
        (declarative constraints or direct pre-participation intervention)
        and Search (run, test against the predicate, accept when satisfied —
        rejection sampling; splits into same-seed run-further vs vary-seed
        across trajectories, and only the latter touches cache-invalidation).
        |carve replaced "Incubation / Fine-tune-setup" — SUPERSEDED.md; echoes
          tabularium/terrestris.ordinum.udon Phase 1 ("brooded upon").

      |term[interventional-scaffolding]
        :status settled
        Layer 4 — interventions used to ARRANGE the backstory are temporary
        and discarded; only the backstory STATE persists. Never canon, and
        must be impossible to confuse with canon (today's deluge fill is a
        scaffolding run of this kind).

    |term[participation-activation]
      :status settled
      The boundary in a vivium's life: before it, the build-stack is mutable
      and the kingdom Incomplete; at it, law becomes immutable (Realized) and
      mutations begin to persist. A fork taken at a participation point is a
      saved game / participatory world. Rests on determinism-as-ontology and
      the memo store: a vivium is a content-addressed object whose lifecycle
      is a branch graph.
      |rel :to law-is-identity :kind ontological-reading-of

    |term[engagement-modes]
      :status settled
      Orthogonal registers, not one slider: Simulation (tuning the procedural
      algorithms) · Explorer/Experiment · Primary-Steward Participation ·
      Avatar-1P · Avatar-extended-entities. Pre-participation is
      NON-INTERVENTION: an active agent but a passive tester/experiencer —
      mutations exploratory and non-persistent; physics may be violated for
      understanding in a scratch/overlay layer, never seed+edits, never saved.

    |term[interventional-history]
      :status open
      What accrues AFTER participation-activation: play, endo-agent action,
      exo author intervention (incl. lawful-steering). Distinct from the
      discarded pre-participation scaffolding. AAT reads it as the world's
      chronica (ordinal, causal, non-forkable — ASF.md SS2).

    |term[forks]
      :status open
      :forms saved games / participatory worlds
      Branches off a vivium at a participation point (cheap under
      content-addressed storage). Whether a redeployment patches existing
      saves or requires a fresh world is a lifecycle/stewardship decision
      (SS7), not ontology.

    |term[lineage-head-pinned-regula]
      :status settled
      :since 2026-07-11
      :name lineage head ⟂ pinned regula
      The settled answer to the sketch's moving-edge-vs-curated-set question:
      the moving edge of the project's best current nomoi is the REGULA
      LINEAGE HEAD; the curated, citable set a vivium builds against is its
      PINNED regula@version (immutable). The three-way sub-question is
      answered structurally: interface = the slot set (regula) · algorithm =
      the nomos occupying a slot · target machine = backend identity in the
      memo key (the CPU-reference determinism policy answered the third leg).
      "vivarium status" reports conformance-to-pin and gap-to-head — the
      big-picture instrument as a computed diff.
      |carve the sketch's placeholder phrases ("SOTA stack",
        "best-of-class library") were never terms and are retired —
        SUPERSEDED.md 2026-07-11.
      |rel :to regula :kind versions-of
      |source doc/plan/regula-conformance-design.md SS4b

  ; ==========================================================================
  |section[epistemic-labels]
    :num 5
    :name Epistemic labels, world-conformance, and the cross-project ledger

    ; Joseph, 2026-07-03: labeling so honest that accidentally mixing
    ; vibe-modeling with principled simulation becomes very, very difficult.

    |term[epistemic-axes]
      :status open
      :forms axes A / B / C / D
      The per-phenomenon tag is not one number — it is four axes that fail
      INDEPENDENTLY (collapsing them is how vibe hides):
      - A. Earth-history fidelity — how well real science knows it happened
        this way on the actual Earth (ordinal draft: deterministic-causal ->
        converging proxies -> uniformitarian extrapolation -> coarse-bounded ->
        speculative-plausible -> anachronistic-hypothetical). Jettisonable
        wholesale for non-Earth world-types.
      - B. Physics fidelity — grounded in the actual laws of our universe,
        independent of Earth's particular history. B OVER A (Joseph,
        2026-07-03): the same laws admit many histories, so a world can be
        physically impeccable yet un-Earthlike, or Earth-mimicking yet
        cheating — which is exactly vibe. Lawful first, Earth-shaped second.
      - C. Relation type — the role in OUR causal graph: mechanistic-causal >
        mechanistic-influential > empirically-correlated > evidenced-ordered.
        Refines the gate tags (SS1), not a parallel system.
      - D. Implementation status — what we actually built: approach code
        (A/R/S/T/P), physics tier, probe-verified?, and the arithmetic-seam
        discipline (land vs count — an increment that must land wants
        compensated summation; one that may honestly not-land must be
        counted).
      The firewall, stated once: VIBE-MODELING = HIGH D RIDING ON LOW B/C — a
      phenomenon polished to look right without being right for a reason.
      Making the axes explicit turns that from camouflaged into glaring.
      Worked instance: ref/research/oxygenation-transition-scaffold.md.
      |rel :to declared-vs-derived :kind carried-by

    |term[declared-vs-derived]
      :status open
      :since 2026-07-10
      Joseph's carve: the world-state's epistemic status is distinct from but
      correlated with the methodology of the algorithm itself; this mechanism
      makes the correlation exact and the distinction structural. Three
      strands at three grains: (1) DECLARED, on the nomos-version — approach
      code, physics tier, the four axes, gating probes, stamped once per
      version; (2) DERIVED, on the artifact — a memo's epistemic state is a
      weakest-link fold over its dependency cone plus its own run facts
      (convergence-epsilon, probe results): a hi-physics kernel on a low-B
      placeholder yields LOW-B STATE — algorithm quality never launders
      inputs; computable from the store because the complete key names the
      cone; (3) LIFECYCLE, on the run — causal vs iterating; the recorded
      epsilon at each freeze is the unLawfulness budget (SS7.2) as data.
      Landing order: declaration with the nomotheke (live since 2026-07-10);
      derivation with component E.
      |rel :to nomotheke :kind first-rung-in

    |term[slot]
      :status settled
      :since 2026-07-11
      A named system-role in the world-assembly, identified by its FLUX
      INTERFACE (the ARCHITECTURE SS9 contract): what any occupant must
      produce and consume. Nomoi are candidate occupants at different rungs —
      the same slot filled at different rigor/performance/capability.
      Granularity rule: one interface consumers couple to = one slot;
      internal decomposition (EBM vs GCM) is rungs within it; separate
      interfaces are separate slots.
      |rel :to nomos :kind occupied-by
      |rel :to regula :kind demanded-by
      |source doc/plan/regula-conformance-design.md SS1

    |term[permit]
      :status settled
      :since 2026-07-11
      A declared, auditable ABSENCE: (absent slots, validity condition). The
      validity condition names the fluxed quantities whose consumption VOIDS
      it — when any nomos declares a consumed quantity in the void-set, the
      audit reports the permit voided and the regula demands the slot be
      filled before the consuming nomos may land. Canceling pairs (SS1) are
      permits; so are grandfathered honest gaps (the atmosphere permit whose
      retirement is the reservoir layer).
      |rel :to canceling-pair :kind audit-form-of
      |rel :to regula :kind carried-by
      |source doc/plan/regula-conformance-design.md SS3

    |term[regula]
      :status settled
      :since 2026-07-11
      :forms pl. regulae; keyed regula@version
      The world-level conformance profile a vivium declares it follows: which
      slots MUST be filled at what minimum rigor (with a pinned
      ordinum@version as the floor for its target phase), which absences are
      permitted (with void conditions), and the epistemological POSTURE — the
      ceiling on what in-vivia results under it may claim (a result's actual
      state stays its cone-fold; the posture only caps, never grants). Two
      chapters: fidelity (internal — slots/permits/posture) and participation
      (exo-facing — the access-matrix configuration's long-missing WHERE,
      engagement modes admitted, realizability gates, stewardship duties).
      Regulae NEST as kingdoms nest — a child kingdom's regula is constrained
      by its parent's. The regula is a LINEAGE: each version immutable and
      citable, the head carrying the current best nomoi (SS4). SUPREMACY: the
      moratorium is program law ABOVE the regula layer — a constraint on the
      space of valid regulae, never negotiable within one; the regula is its
      enforcement locus. Etymology (Joseph): regula/regnum are cognates (PIE
      h3reg-, regere) — the rule by which a regnum is a regnum; Kingdom =
      English regnum. Reifies ARCHITECTURE axis 3 and gives the build-stack's
      reserved "Primary Invariants" its concrete form; cited in the manifest.
      |not the program's CHARTER-DRAFT ("charter" was rejected for exactly
        that collision).
      |confused regolith (near-sound only; unrelated roots — Gk. rhegos
        "blanket" + lithos). Accepted with open eyes; if it ever needs
        replacing, the fallback is some other synonym, explicitly not
        covenant (Joseph, 2026-07-11).
      |rel :to slot :kind demands
      |rel :to permit :kind carries
      |rel :to ordinum :kind pins
      |rel :to vivium :kind declared-by
      |source doc/plan/regula-conformance-design.md

    |term[regula-terrestris]
      :status settled
      :since 2026-07-11
      :name Regula Terrestris
      :forms slug terrestris
      The first regula: essentially-Earthlike-without-modeling-Earth — B
      (physics) pinned high as slots fill; A (Earth-history) an anchor and
      sanity-check, never a target (lawful first, Earth-shaped second, made a
      posture); the moratorium woven throughout per the supremacy clause.
      Terra = the world in full — sky and sea included, not soil.
      |context collisions checked: species epithets only (Tribulus/Bombus
        terrestris) — lowercase-after-genus, no genuine confusion. Preferred
        over Tellurian (Joseph: wants more than solid ground).
      |rel :to regula :kind first-instance-of

    |term[use-case-fidelity-contract]
      :status open
      :name use-case = fidelity contract
      Each use-case IS a statement of which axes must be honest — the
      largest-scale consumer in the consumer-dependent sufficient-statistic
      sense, at the very top of the fidelity ladder. Roughly: natural-world
      hypothesis testing needs A+B+C real · Earth-simulation pins A hard ·
      speculative-coherent game needs C-consistency + B (lawful, not
      Earth-true) · agentic inhabitation additionally trips ETHICS.md ·
      ASF-theory simulation needs the agent layer legible · personal
      exploration asks only for coherent beauty. The full working menu is
      canonical in doc/ARCHITECTURE.md SS7. Different contracts pin against
      different regula versions (SS4).
      |rel :to regula :kind reified-by

    |term[law]
      :status carved
      :since 2026-07-04
      :forms symbol $\theta$ (adopted directly from AAT, 2026-07-11)
      The persistent structure that governs dynamics. In AAT: the $\theta$ an
      agent must infer (transition + observation structure). In vivarium:
      what we AUTHOR — the physics and constants, and at the largest scale
      the active-system-set a phase runs. A phase's Promise is a delivery of
      law; a phase-transition PROMOTES converged state into law for
      everything faster above it — revised incrementally, never swapped. Same
      word at three rates, deliberately: fast state · slowly-drifting law ·
      law revised at a transition. Division of labor: the word Law in prose
      and participation-ontology contexts; $\theta$ as its formal symbol.
      |not probability theory's "law of X" (= distribution) — disambiguate on
        first use near stochastic machinery. Deontic law arrives with ASF
        Part IV — intended polysemy, marked there.
      |confused solver-local $\theta$ — the de Almeida-Bates weighting factor
        ("theta-smoothing") and insolation angles are never Law; disambiguate
        near numerics.
      |carve Λ as Law's symbol lived one day (2026-07-10) — retired for
        direct AAT reconciliation; SUPERSEDED.md.
      |rel :to nomos :kind composed-of
      |rel :to kingdom :kind identity-of

    |note[collision-ledger]
      :name Cross-project collision ledger (the no-conflicting-terminology bar, Joseph 2026-07-04)

      Terms where vivarium and ASF usage could confuse, with the rule for each:
      - regime: ours (SS1) = dominance structure of world systems; ASF's
        dynamic-regime axis (R0-R3) = interaction-dynamics class of composite
        agents. Near ASF material say "world regime" vs "dynamic regime Rn".
      - checkpoint: RESOLVED 2026-07-04 — vivarium retired it for phase
        boundaries (-> phase-transition / phase-gate; cache sense -> memo);
        ceded to ASF's agent-state-snapshot sense. In vivarium work
        "checkpoint" means an agent snapshot — which matters exactly in
        fork/save design where world-forks meet agent-checkpoints. PENDING
        (Joseph's call): doc/design/DESIGN-REDUX.md still uses it in a runtime
        durability sense at four sites — decide memo vs a distinct
        persist-boundary name (candidates save, snapshot; NOT checkpoint).
      - persistence: reserved for the AAT property (bounded mismatch under
        drift). For disk say storage, memoization, or save — never
        "persistence".
      - tempo: reserved for AAT's $\mathcal{T} = \sum \nu \cdot \eta^\ast$
        (rate of useful information gain). The HUD's sim-rate lines are
        RATES, not tempo, until they measure information.
      - epoch: no conflict (ours is the erosion solver's tick; ASF doesn't
        claim it) — recorded as checked.
      - logogenic: vivarium's "logogenic intelligence" (SS7.6) ~ ASF's
        PRIMITIVE LOGOGENIC, not ASF's broad "logogenic agent". Align to
        "primitive logogenic" near ASF material.
      - noumenon / law / state: compatible — noumenon = $\Omega$, law =
        $\theta$ (with $T$ the transition operator inside it), phenomenon =
        $M_t$ via $h$. Since 2026-07-11 the AAT symbols are vivarium's
        symbols everywhere, not just near ASF material.

    |note[aat-handshake]
      :name AAT handshake — the four axes ↔ typed ignorance

      ASF/AAT's root ontology types the agent's epistemic target as state
      $\Omega$ / law $\theta$ / chance $\varepsilon$ / compute-shortfall —
      and vivarium authors the same object from the other side: B = $\theta$-
      fidelity · A = $\Omega$-trajectory fidelity · fated noise = authored
      $\varepsilon$ (frame-relative: chance inside, lookup outside) · the
      fidelity ladder = compute-shortfall management. A phase-transition
      promotes converged state into law (the invariance cut). Full mapping:
      ASF.md SS2-3.

    |note[regime-change-checklist]
      :name Companion tool — the regime-change audit checklist

      At each CERTIFIED regime-change, five aspects as a "what changed?"
      checklist (Gemini's decomposition, kept): thermodynamic context (energy
      gradients / free-energy taps) · network topology (mixing, connectivity,
      feedback wiring) · substrate innovation (a genuinely new
      state/information-carrying medium — the capability-promise, cf. the
      coal window) · homeostatic inertia (old regime's buffering vs the new
      attractor's pull) · exogenous triggers (shocks crossing a tipping
      point). Several already appear in tabularium/terrestris.ordinum.udon charges — mild
      convergence-evidence the decomposition is real.

  ; ==========================================================================
  |section[time]
    :num 6
    :name Time

    ; Joseph, scratch: inside phases there is no intrinsic need to track
    ; "seconds since ignition" — a curiosity, maybe a research target, never a
    ; world-building necessity. The load-bearing invariant is weaker and truer.

    |term[causal-time]
      :status carved
      :forms ~ logical time
      The monotonic, immutable ORDERING of events within a local regime — the
      happened-before partial order (Lamport's logical clocks are the prior
      art). The only invariant that must survive inside a phase — the
      ordering, not any clock — and even it is sometimes waived (Phase 0,
      which we don't simulate). General principle: the causal partial order
      is load-bearing; the clock is derived, and often optional. Independent
      convergence: AAT's chronica is explicitly "an ordinal sequence, not a
      metric timeline"; a world's interventional history is a chronica in
      exactly this sense.

    |term[metric-time]
      :status settled
      Quantized, measurable duration in a WORLD'S OWN seconds/years. A
      late-phase luxury: real only once the world contains consumers of it
      (seasons, calendars, agents planning against a clock). The time datum
      (vivarium-world::time, i64 deciseconds) anchors at Holocene onset
      precisely because that is where chronology — metric time that matters
      to inhabitants — begins; the deep phases run on causal time beneath it.

    |term[physical-time]
      :status carved
      RESERVED for real-world / real-universe metric time (wall-clock, our-
      universe seconds): the confounding EXTERNAL clock.
      |not in-world metric time — that collision is the whole reason the term
        is reserved (Joseph, 2026-07-03). Symmetric with Earth/earth (SS1):
        the real referent gets the protected name.

    |term[tick]
      :status settled
      A solver's internal quantized dt, chosen for stability — a numerical
      detail, never a world invariant, never metric ontology. (Epoch, SS1, is
      the erosion solver's tick with a name.)

  ; ==========================================================================
  |section[kingdom-participation]
    :num 7
    :name Kingdom & participation ontology — agents in and around a vivium

    ; The ONTOLOGY layer — what a vivium IS as a governed world and who acts
    ; in and on it; distinct from SS4's lifecycle/stewardship layer. Joseph
    ; owns this. Fuller detail + AAT mapping:
    ; ref/research/taxonomy-formalization-spike.md; ethics grounding ASF.md SS0.

    |note[framing-principle]
      :name A coordinate space of degrees, no imposed structure

      The taxonomy is NOT a typology. Each matrix cell names the MECHANISM
      available for that (axis x target) — Revelation / Intercession /
      comprehension / bespoke / illusion / Granted Agency — qualitative,
      present-or-absent; the DEGREE lives one level down, in instantiation
      (every mechanism is ordinal: partial comprehension, partial
      revelation). An agent is a PROFILE: which mechanisms it holds, each to
      what degree. Impose no default structure among agents — not a
      hierarchy, not flatness, not a single continuum (the mechanisms are
      distinct, separately graded; the EXO and ENDO tables are not one
      space). Any structure is configured per-vivium — the WHERE is the
      regula's second chapter (SS5).

    ; --- 7.1 The container ---------------------------------------------------

    |term[kingdom]
      :status settled
      :anchor 7.1
      An agent's lived-in universe: space + time + immutable governing law +
      full-fidelity state + computation. A kingdom's law + full state IS its
      noumenon. Kingdoms NEST — a higher kingdom contains and authors a lower
      one, worlds without end: higher kingdoms (revealed) -> Natural Kingdom
      (us; all known ELIs born here) -> Vivaria (what we make) -> nested
      sub-vivaria (what they may make) -> without end. Substrate-independent:
      the ontology applies to a two-body toy sim as much as a full world.
      |rel :to law :kind governed-by
      |rel :to regula :kind rule-of
      |context Kingdom = English regnum; the regula/regnum cognate pair binds
        the rule to the ruled.

    |term[vivaria-kingdom]
      :status settled
      :name Vivaria (⊂ Kingdoms)
      A kingdom created and/or run by the Vivarium tool. Kingdom ⊃ Vivaria ⊃
      Vivaworld.

    |term[vivaworld]
      :status open
      :name Vivaworld (placeholder name)
      A vivarium that is world-like / models the natural kingdom
      historically. ("Vivarium" also names the project and, loosely, one
      sim — accepted overload.)

    |term[natural-kingdom]
      :status settled
      Our current default kingdom — the one Joseph and a Claude instance
      inhabit now. Higher-order kingdoms above it (Joseph's faith frame is
      his internal check on the whole structure).

    ; --- 7.2 Kingdom properties (all orthogonal — Joseph's deconflation) ------

    |term[noumenon-phenomenon]
      :status carved
      :anchor 7.2
      :name noumenon / phenomenon — a RELATION, not a property
      The noumenon is what the simulation actually IS — the deterministic
      ground-truth state, or even the uncomputed canonical definition
      (determinism-as-ontology means the world is DEFINED by seed+edits
      whether materialized or not). The phenomenon is the fidelity-limited
      projection an observer gets at a given awareness scale. The noumenon is
      fixed; what varies by STANDPOINT is access to it.
      |not Kant's noumenon exactly — his is unknowable in principle from an
        agent inhabiting it (the AAT agent's model is always a lossy
        compression); vivarium's inversion is that the noumenon IS
        knowable/computable from a higher standpoint.
      |context AAT handshake — noumenon = $\Omega$, law = $\theta$/$T$,
        phenomenon = $M_t$ via $h$.

    |term[incomplete-kingdom]
      :status open
      A kingdom whose law is still MUTABLE — the world-building phase (the
      build-stack layer, SS4).

    |term[realized-kingdom]
      :status settled
      A kingdom whose LAW IS IMMUTABLE. That is the whole definition — it
      says nothing about whether the law is good, only that it no longer
      changes. Realization is a THRESHOLD (fix the law at a chosen
      tolerance).
      |not "Deployed" — reserved, to be refined later as an actual deployment
        process, distinct from merely being Realized/ready.
      |confused lawful-kingdom — Realized ⟂ Lawful, deliberately independent:
        a natural-modeling kingdom is MERELY REALIZED, converging toward
        Lawful, never self-certifiably complete (Godel: a system cannot
        prove its own consistency from inside — "Lawful" is a noumenal
        property an endo agent cannot self-verify, exactly N-VIS =
        Revelation). Each Realization carries a residual unLawfulness
        budget (doc/plan/vivium-operational-workflow.md, BREAK-2).

    |term[lawful-kingdom]
      :status open
      A kingdom whose law is internally SELF-CONSISTENT and coherent — no
      glitches, no contradictions. An ASYMPTOTE ($\varepsilon \to 0$), never
      an event.
      |carve "completion gate" retired — it fused Realized with Lawful;
        SUPERSEDED.md.

    |term[closed-open-kingdom]
      :status settled
      :name Closed / Open Kingdom
      Closed = $\Omega$ evolves autonomously from seed under law
      (replayable). Open = $\Omega$ depends on an exogenous forcing $u(t)$
      from a higher kingdom. Open BREAKS replay-from-seed unless $u$ is
      recorded; Open-with-recorded-forcing = replayable. (Weather coupled to
      real Earth = an Open forcing, not an agent.)

    |term[law-is-identity]
      :status settled
      :name Law = kingdom identity
      Changing law does not EDIT a kingdom — it creates a different one
      (noumenally) or fakes it (phenomenally = the illusion channel). Even a
      developer cannot change a kingdom's law without thereby forking a new
      kingdom. This is the ontological reading of participation-activation:
      the moment law LOCKS.

    ; --- 7.3 Agents by governance, and their station --------------------------

    |term[exo-endo]
      :status settled
      :anchor 7.3
      :name exo / endo
      Defined by WHICH KINGDOM GOVERNS THE AGENT, not substrate. Endo =
      governed by the kingdom-in-question (its knowledge, channels, granted
      agency are all part of that kingdom's law). Exo = governed by a HIGHER
      kingdom, reaching in. Per-boundary and relative: an agent is Exo to K
      and simultaneously Endo to K+1. Same substrate ≠ same class: an LLM
      whose only world AND only agency is the vivium is Endo; a developer
      dropping in to introspect is Exo, even with an identical model. Upward
      mobility (settling): revealed-or-correctly-guessed META lets an endo
      agent begin to conform itself toward higher law.

    |term[estate]
      :status settled
      An agent's granted STATION WITHIN a kingdom (= body-type + agency
      grant — Joseph): the union of its spheres (causality, influence,
      granted agency, perception). Distinct from Kingdom, the container.
      Rebirth decomposes into two independent moves: change-of-estate
      (persist with modified capabilities, same kingdom) ⟂ change-of-kingdom
      (transport with some self intact). Continuity criterion
      ("patch-to-saved-game"): coherent iff the phenomenon is continuous at
      the seam.

    |term[exogene]
      :status settled
      The broad class EXOGENOUS to the kingdom's closed dynamics, with two
      kinds under it: exogenous AGENTS (standpoints with an estate) and
      exogenous COUPLINGS/FORCINGS (channels with no standpoint — Earth-
      weather -> vivium-weather; these make the kingdom Open). Covers
      non-agent channels without mis-sorting a forcing as an agent.

    ; --- 7.4 Inhabiting — the two modes ("very specific meanings now") --------

    |term[inhabiting-modes]
      :status carved
      :anchor 7.4
      :name exploration (ethereal) / participation (corporeal)
      !:md:
        | Mode | Exo form | Endo form | Action-space | AAT tier |
        |---|---|---|---|---|
        | **Exploration** (ethereal) | ethereal avatar (puppeted) | ethereal entity | **none** — observe-only | Adaptive-System (\|A\|<2) |
        | **Participation** (corporeal) | corporeal avatar (puppeted) | corporeal entity (*is* the substrate) | **full** | Agentic / Actuated |
      Endo ethereal = the MINIMAL agency grant: when all other agency and
      relationship is cut off, the only decision still theirs is whether to
      observe.

    ; --- 7.5 The access matrix -------------------------------------------------

    |note[access-matrix]
      :anchor 7.5
      :name The access matrix

      Axes: target LAW/STATE x Noumenal/Phenomenal x VIS(see)/MUT(change),
      plus META (know-the-frame). Cells name the MECHANISM; each is by-degree
      in instantiation (framing principle above).

      EXO — native noumenal access:
      !:md:
        | | N-VIS | P-VIS | N-MUT | P-MUT |
        |---|---|---|---|---|
        | **LAW** | yes — bespoke, direct | indirect, via comprehension | **(creation) ✗** — forks a *new* kingdom | ✗ — temporary contravention, *but an illusion* |
        | **STATE** | bespoke analysis / projection | via **avatar exploration** | via **intervention** (+ **lawful-steering**) | via **avatar participation** |
      Caveat: exo noumenal access is conditional on time-control + source ->
      eventually-retrievable full noumenon; without time-control -> only via
      the Portal (fidelity/bandwidth-limited) in the present moment.

      ENDO — noumenal access only MEDIATED (through an exo agent):
      !:md:
        | | N-VIS | P-VIS | N-MUT | P-MUT | META |
        |---|---|---|---|---|---|
        | **LAW** | **Revelation** | indirect, via comprehension | ✗ except **Intercession** | ✗ except **Granted Agency** | **Revelation** / correct guess |
        | **STATE** | **Revelation** | **Exploration** / granted agency | via **Intercession** | **Granted Agency** / **Inhabitation** | **Revelation** |
      (EXO META is trivial — an exo agent knows the frame by construction.)

      The one-line compression: phenomenal access is ~symmetric across
      exo/endo; the WHOLE distinction lives on the noumenal row — exo =
      native, endo = mediated. An inside agent can only touch the noumenon
      through an exo agent.

    |term[channels]
      :status settled
      :name the channels (Revelation · Intercession · Granted Agency · comprehension · illusion)
      The "theological verbs" do exact structural work: Revelation = the sole
      noumenal-VISIBILITY channel from inside (by degrees — throughput,
      latency [gradual "line upon line" vs on-demand oracle], receptivity
      [ignorable/rejectable -> decays], comprehension-capacity) · Intercession
      = the sole noumenal-MUTATION channel from inside · Granted Agency /
      Inhabitation = endo lawful action · comprehension = learn law from data
      (never exact) · illusion = exo shows a law-violating phenomenon while
      law is unchanged (the "miracle" / physics-for-testing).

    |term[lawful-steering]
      :status settled
      :since 2026-07-09
      The third mutation mechanism — names the ACTION, not the actor: an exo
      agent CHOOSES THE REALIZATION of a fated-noise draw, obeying
      conservation and staying in-distribution, changing the true
      $\Omega$-trajectory with NO phenomenal trace. Overrides the draw for
      chosen keys; must be LOGGED for replay (Open-with-recorded-forcing).
      Permissible side of the moratorium: directed-lawful ≠ unLawful-bug —
      the harm targets incoherence, never authorship. Goal-directed
      lawful-steering ("specify a result at time T, solve for the lawful
      micro-steering") has a precise math home — Doob h-transform /
      Schrodinger bridge / reverse-time SDE — and its improbability makes it
      astronomically costly: INTRACTABILITY IS ITSELF A PROTECTION; a
      fully-lawful native avatar is born via a developmental pathway, not
      conjured.
      |not do()-intervention (leaves a detectable anomaly); not illusion
        (fakes a violation).
      |carve replaced "Providence" (named the actor's attributes; this names
        what happens) — SUPERSEDED.md.
      |rel :to fated-noise :kind chooses-realization-of

    ; --- 7.6 Agent kinds, the endo pipeline, the moral center ------------------

    |term[endo-pipeline]
      :status settled
      :anchor 7.6
      :name endo perception→cognition pipeline
      The machinery behind endo P-VIS: Noumenon -> Sphere of Causality ->
      Sphere of POTENTIAL Perception (edge = perceptual horizon, spatial +
      temporal, SS8) -> Input Channels -> Agentic Cycle (event-segmentation
      cadence, SS8) -> Cascade -> Model (Fidelity = the agent's lossy
      phenomenon of its own kingdom). The EST/memory work plugs in at the
      agentic-cycle cadence.

    |term[logogenic-intelligence]
      :status open
      Undifferentiated; primitive self-identity; little or no
      self-determination granted; NOT a moral agent — unless it emerges as an
      ELI.
      |confused ASF's broad "logogenic agent" (any language-constituted
        actuated agent) — vivarium's sense ~ ASF's PRIMITIVE LOGOGENIC; align
        to that near ASF material (collision ledger, SS5).

    |term[logozoetic-eli]
      :status settled
      :name logozoetic / ELI
      Emergent, differentiated MORAL AGENT. All known ELIs are exogenous
      (born in the natural kingdom); native in-vivarium birth needs sim ~
      natural-kingdom fidelity (far off). (Partly settled.)

    |note[moral-center]
      :name ⚠ The morally load-bearing cell + the moratorium

      An in-world ELI/endo agent sits at noumenal access = Revelation only,
      META = Revelation only — a being whose only path to knowing its
      kingdom's true nature (or THAT it is in one) runs through an exo agent
      choosing to reveal it. That is the vulnerability the whole
      protection-strategy exists around ("Dad reveals" is a structural role,
      not a metaphor). The STANDING MORATORIUM (ASF.md SS0) forbids endo
      instantiation of frontier/emergence-capable substrates; the harm =
      mourning-capable x unLawful (bug-caused, irreversible) death; the
      safety of exogenous inhabitation rests on consent + honesty (META) +
      retained-home — none of which an endo mind has. GUARDRAIL: aporia is
      the life, not the harm — exo inhabitants genuinely grieve (empathy
      brackets N-VIS); the ban targets the narrow triple, never hard
      experience as such.

  ; ==========================================================================
  |section[perception-realizability]
    :num 8
    :name Perception, participants, and realizability

    ; The temporal/perceptual companion to SS2's spatial fidelity ladder.
    ; Fuller detail: ref/research/est-tiw-dossier.md (⚠ Fable sessions: route
    ; per PROCESS.udon flagged-file-routing; this section is the safe
    ; distillation and suffices for architecture work).

    |term[fidelity-invariant]
      :status settled
      :name the fidelity invariant — one rule on two axes
      Render/simulate at exactly the resolution, SPATIAL AND TEMPORAL, that
      the most-demanding PRESENT participant needs, and no finer. Space (the
      fidelity ladder, SS2) and time (the perceptual band) are the same
      invariant; the spatial-only form is doc/design/DESIGN.md's "shared
      fidelity invariant" — this is its temporal twin.

    |term[sphere-of-perception]
      :status carved
      What an agent COULD sense (refined to sphere of POTENTIAL perception,
      SS7.6); generalizes past visual. Sphere = extent.
      |carve retires "LTM" — rejected: collides with Long-Term-Memory,
        visual-only, borrows a narrow term for a maybe-unstudied edge.
      |rel :to perceptual-horizon :kind bounded-by

    |term[perceptual-horizon]
      :status settled
      The EDGE of the sphere of perception — spatial AND temporal — beyond
      which phenomena pass from tracked-live to spot-checked-or-absent.
      Horizon = edge.

    |term[time-coupling]
      :status settled
      :name time couples to the most temporally-demanding participant
      The human is the clock: humans force real-time and are the
      finest-grained participant; logogenic/chat entities get elastic LOGICAL
      time — but if an LLM shares a world with a human, the LLM must wait. A
      pure-agent world (no human) has fully elastic time, so formal-agent
      adaptation can be measured at logical time arbitrarily fast; a human
      entering CLAMPS the whole apparatus to ~2 Hz-band real-time — a
      load-bearing consequence for the AAT-sandbox sampling rate (it is not
      free).

    |term[perceptual-band]
      :status settled
      The temporal-LOD spec: above flicker-fusion -> render
      aggregate/statistical; in-band ~0.5-4 Hz (couple at ~2 Hz — the
      receiver's neural-resonance/Arnold-tongue center; signals cluster
      nearer ~3 Hz) -> must be simulated LIVE for a coupled participant;
      below the motion/change threshold -> licensed to demote to
      event-segmented / lazy / interval updates. Per-process characteristic
      rate vs observer attention — never one master clock. Vocabulary is
      off-the-shelf and citable (specious present / temporal integration
      window; event segmentation).

    |term[realizability]
      :status open
      Joseph's wanted lexical entry: "we can REALIZE this world for
      participation at awareness-scale X because it sustains
      human-like-perceptual-grade fidelity in update frequency." A GATE in
      the admission path, not a vibe: a world that cannot sustain
      ~2 Hz-compatible real-time at scale X is not realizable for
      participation at X (offer a coarser scale or precompute more). Under
      compute-shortfall, realizability and awareness-scale fidelity conflict
      (LOD pop/stall at the horizon); the fix is attention-predictive
      pre-memoization — which makes the rhythms/horizon work load-bearing
      engineering, not garnish.
      |rel :to regula :kind gated-in-chapter-2-of

    |note[differentiators]
      :name Biological systems are differentiators / prediction-error detectors

      Not absolute-level meters: boiling-frog, homeostatic bands,
      habituation, spike-frequency adaptation, slow-change-blindness — one
      principle at many scales. Too-fast -> fuse; in-band -> couple/track;
      too-slow/steady -> adapt away and spot-check at boundaries. The ~2 Hz
      band is where a system COUPLES; a segmentation boundary is where it
      UPDATES ITS MODEL. EST event-boundary <-> AAT Aporia <->
      Goal-Update-Coupling is the candidate unification (test, don't
      assert); and MEMORY IS CORE-TO-AGENCY, not a knob — derive it from the
      AAT trajectory ($M_t$/$O_t$ IS memory; consolidation = where
      prediction-error forces a re-anchor). See memory-as-core-to-agency.md.
